They have a whole section devoted to the condemnation of space colonies and space mining. <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.globenet.free-online.co.uk/scandmen.htm">Space colonies BAD for us</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->. This includes a re-post of a space.com article entitled <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.globenet.free-online.co.uk/articles/moving.htm"> Survival of the Elitist: Bioterrorism may Spur Space Colonies</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->. This echoes long-standing anti-nuclear opposition to any effort that places individual survival above collective interest. (They, of course, are the arbiters of collective interest.)<br>
     In this case, the article's title is of greater importance than its content; containing, as it does, the political trigger word &quot;elitist&quot;. In the world of authoritarian rhetoric, titles and other sound-bites are always more important than meaningful content, as we see in the endless lists of command-mode slogans that infest the GnawAnPis website. This is a kind of cant, and it is a necessary feature of all authoritarian cults, from Hare Krishnas to Communists. <br>
They call us a priesthood, but you don't find our supporters standing around chanting like a bunch of medieval monks. Even when we do come up with a good sound bite, (&quot;more nukes, fewer kooks&quot;), it is either stolen from a wacko cult* that happens to support nuclear power, or it is a kind of parody of anti-nuke-speak.  <br>
<br>
*Lyndon LaRouche in this case, though the original was &quot;more nukes, less kooks&quot;. I felt a compelling need to correct his grammar. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/ubestonnet.showPublicProfile?language=EN>bestonnet</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fusion Starship Captain</span><br>  Posts: 390<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(3/23/02 10:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: GnawAnPis condemns space colonies</span><hr size=1> I though space colonies were in the collective interest?<br>
