Unless you're from VHEM. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=x>X</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Space Tourist</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(3/26/02 3:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Understand everything from an extreme environmentalists POV</span><hr size=1> You see, mankind is a natural plague upon nature.  Our mere existance is an abomination upon the universe.  We spoil anything we touch.  That's why so many national parks are closed off for visitors: less we taint it.  The Earth must be quarentined to keep mankind from infesting the rest of the Universe.  Only when you see the world though the eyes of environmentalist extremists will you realize the reasoning behind their actions and redirick (spelling?). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uprojectorion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>projectorion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Nuclear Renaissance Man</span><br>  Posts: 794<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(3/27/02 12:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.fas.org/nuke/hew/Usa/Tests/Rwmohawk2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~nuclearspace/ezboard/images/posticons/Bart-term.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Understand everything from an extreme environmentalists </span><hr size=1> Rhetoric? I get so sick of hearing their nonsense about humans not being responsible enough to move into space. Who are they to decide such things? If we have the know how and choose to take the challenge there is little we could do to 'damage' space even if it was our mission. The endless millions of kilometres of void between worlds is a deep ocean of radioactive solar winds and the barren planets mere uninhabitable deserts. We truly have no concept of how tiny we are in the great scheme of things. This pitiful little rock called Earth may be the largest terrestrial planet but it would easily fit inside of Jupiters Red Spot. The sun could swallow a thousand Earths and not show a hiccup. All the nuclear waste we produce is just trace heavy elements scratched out of the Earths crust. Moved around then tapped and buried. This entire planet is just a small part of the left over remnants from a single dead star. <br>
We delude ourselves if we think we really have any influence on the universe's machinations or possibly could. Remembere the movie Ants where the workers are celebrating their title of 'rulers of the Earth' over a few drinks at the local bar?<br>
<br>
That's us. <br>
<br>
We are even less than we could be. By ignoring nuclear power we limit our technological base. Thereby placing a constraint on our progress which ensures we can't elevate to the next stage in development.<br>
<br>
Sure. We have the bomb and we believe this last measure weapon only technology can save us should push come to shove against anything that will ever threaten us. What if we're wrong? What if other ants in the universe took the next step and when we meet them they aren't friendly? The military is often accused of shooting first and asking questions later.<br>
<br>
This is actually a very sound approach to any potential threat. A spacefaring species might deem any intelligent race a potential future threat and take the logical step of making certain that potential is never realised. <br>
<br>
Perhaps what we need is an Alien threat. Nothing else could unite the Earth and get serious space travel happening. Unfortunately, if they had the technology to cross interstellar space and actually planned our demise there would be absolutely nothing we could do to stop them. Forget the Hollywood atomic bombs saving the day. To a nuclear power embracing Alien race the primitive bombs we use would be laughable. They would probably be carrying anti-matter devices capable of incinerating the Earth or even possibly snuffing out the sun. <p>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
<br>Nuclear power is the next logical step for serious space travel. The technology required to colonise the solar system exists now!

